  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to assess which of two commonly used surgical procedures in the
      treatment of ovarian cysts called endometriomas (cutting out of the cyst - &quot;cystectomy&quot;, or
      draining it and cauterising it's inner lining - &quot;ablation&quot;) causes the least damage to the
      ovary and is therefore best at maintaining the future fertility potential of a patient.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
